There are only a small number, but that is enough.
There are moments when you try to exceed the required number of opponents (as in a classic race) and then run against the watch (traditional double with the chronometer) and then again awaits you another duel with an opponent.
From time to time you also have the police who enter the game and who try to make the situation difficult for you.
The novelty is the out-of-vehicle passages.
It's more of an interactive animation when most of the time Jack runs away in front of someone and you have to help him by hitting the right button at the right time.
Nothing complicated.
