The result is as well as this because this element is not likely to hinder and places, in the context described above, in the elements that decorate the game.
The driving model is in the tradition of previous games.
This means that there is currently nothing extraordinary but it cannot be said to be negative.
As far as realistic simulation is concerned, you will have to go somewhere else.
But although it is possible to find better in the competition the model of conduct is very well with the type of design of the races.
So everything's okay.
Problems begin to appear after some time.
At the differference of the driving model, the collision model is not yet up to date.
We do not expect from this game a complicated deformation and collisions, but when you do not have, during a collision with any object, the slightest idea of how your car behaves, it is therefore not completely good.
During tight exceedances you sometimes touch each other slightly but otherwise your self part in crazy volts.
Or it's in crumbs.
Thanks to the restart system this is not really a problem but it really annoys you.
The restart is done so that when you have broken the figure or you have come out in the decor the game brings you back at the last point on the itinerary.
But you only have 5 reboots.
When you used the 5 restarts you have to start the game again from the beginning.
So it's more of a tool, in case something doesn't go as it should, than something you can really count on.
Sometimes the restarts do not help and the solution must be found by remembering the piece of itinerary in question.
The great hic of this game is that the same actions are found in the same places.
