You need to pay attention to petrol pumps on the routes as you can change cars however most of the time you have enough.
The cars are divided into three categories.
Sports cars are ideal for cities, large American cylinders for right highways and super sports cars with exotic attractions on very technical pipes, for example on lancet roads in the mountains.
And the mode of challenges, which are races in particular places that you know about adventure, goes very well with the main regime of history.
You receive not only medals but also points of experience that add to your profile that is common to challenges and adventure.
When you have reached the highest level of driver, different objects begin to unlock:
This one connects online with the Autolog function that, among other things, compares your results with those of other players and provides you with other functions in the community.
One of the most difficult blows to understand is the situation of the last race of adventure.
You arrive with your car in the tunnel of the metro (ca similar) where you run in the darkness on the tracks (ca similar).
Your speed indicator shows you between 150 and 200 km/hour (a priori) and behind you comes a subway branch that sends you the car directly to the scrap metal.
In writing we had a discussion for a few days about whether someone really thought about the creation of this game or whether the authors really take us for imbeciles.
The technical part of the game is not extra, but the visual part is generally pleasant and in some cases really great.
What bothers is that in more extreme situations, imagery does not hold the level and in some cases tragically.
This mainly concerns accidents with a large number of participants when a fluid imagery no longer serves you anything.
The sound game is good and the track is chosen.
In order to please the greatest number and especially the young audience a new soundtrack was created in the style "I mix everything", but one can expect that no one will buy the game for music.
General Impression of Need for Speed: The Run is therefore very confusing.
If the game did not have these stupid mistakes we could say without fear that it is the best production of NFS in recent years.
But this game gives the impression that it is not finished.
The fun is really good, but prepare yourself for the faults hitting you in the eyes with the strength of an aerodrome reflector.
The students of velvet in concert with the choirs of Charles University
The Festival Festa Academica offers for the third time festivals that connect the International Student Day with the anniversary of the Velvet Revolution with a musical part.
During the festival there are 20 choirs of higher schools and secondary classes.
The highlight of the festival consists of two concerts organized on November 17th.
"Charles University has an important part in this festival."
"Through the choirs there is the Choir of the Faculty of Pedagogy and Humanities, in the festival committee is the rector Vaclav Hampl", says the head of the organizing team Jakub Calou.
The key to the festival is the Choeur des lycées et gradués concert, which takes place with free entry on 17 November from 14 hours on the space located in front of the National Technical Library in Dejvice.
On the program there is the composition of the well-known Czech jazzman Karel Ruzicka, Celebration Jazz mass.
In the evening the concert "Students of velvet" takes place in the premises of the National House in Vinohrady during which the choirs of higher schools and that of Charles University are held.
The aim of the Festa Academica is not only to celebrate with dignity the International Student Day and to recall the 22nd anniversary of the Velvet Revolution, but also to present to the public a choir music of the highest level and to develop the creative cooperation of young people.
The main organiser is the Union of Czech Charities in cooperation with Jan Kepler High School.
All the action is under the aegis of Bohuslav Svoboda, Mayor of Prague and Vaclav Hampl, Rector of Charles University.
The festival takes place from November 16 to 20 in Prague and Pardubice.
The program also offers high-level concerts, msical meetings, student arrivals and other activities.
Interested parties will find all information on the website of the festival www.festaacademica.cz.
