IBM (International Business Machines) was born in New York a hundred years ago; it initially had the complicated name of Computing Tabulation Recording Corporation.
She took the name IBM in 1924 - initially it was a trademark used by a branch of a firm in Canada and South America.
The foundation of the future IBM was the merger of four firms whose history is linked to the years 80 of the nineteenth century.
