These questions, he stressed, "required the operation of a whole system establishes, in accordance with the principle of economic direction of the State, a group of allocations which the Constitution grants to the faculty of the Executive of the State".
He recalled that a large number of countries around the world have already completed the digital transition and have done so through the Executive, despite the fact that they have highly specialized technical bodies.
It cannot be concluded that the Executive, by issuing the contested decree, has somehow invaded the sphere of competence of Congress, as it ensures in the administrative sphere respect for the laws issued by the Legislative, it will.
The possibility of a "vote by vote" count in Michoacán is analysed.
According to the data highlighted by PREP, the difference between the first and second place of the Governor's election is only 27 percent, even without counting the votes corresponding to the 879 of the 6 thousand 74 total minutes.
The possibility of the "vote by vote" count is a reality with respect to the electoral trial this year in Michoacán, where according to the data highlighted by the Preliminary Electoral Results Program (PREP) the difference between the first and second place of the governor's election is only 27 percent, even without counting the votes corresponding to the 879 of the 6 thousand 74 total minutes.
In this sense, the President of the General Council of the Electoral Institute of Michoacán (IEM), María de los Angeles Llanderal Zaragoza, recalled that a few days ago, on 9 November, the electoral body approved a series of guidelines to harmonize local standards with federal electoral reform.
It will be recalled that Michoacán has not approved either its Political Constitution or its Electoral Code or its Electoral Justice Act, while the Congress of the State has approved reforms shortly before the end of the legal period for this electoral trial to enter into force and Governor Leonel Godoy Rangel has omitted its publication within the time limits provided for by the Law of the Official Journal of the State, with the argument that he had some objections.
On 9 November, the Supreme Court of Justice of the Nation (SCJN) resolved the constitutional controversy promoted by the Local Legislative Power and called the vote of the state attorney for constitutional reforms "invalid and illegal" because he does not have the right to "sanction or contest".
Interviewed on the possibility of the "vote by vote", María de los Ángeles Llanderal said that through the approval of the corresponding guidelines by the General Council of IEM it will be possible to realize the partial and total discounts of the votes by the local electoral body.
Thus, the partial count of votes, of one or more electoral packages, it may be that: the results of the minutes do not coincide; there is no record of the vote and count in the record of the ballot box is not found in the president of the ballot box; or there are obvious errors or alterations in the minutes.
In addition, the total count of the votes received in all polls of the election may be made when there is an indication that the difference between the alleged candidate winning the respective election and the candidate obtaining the second place in the poll is equal to or below a percentage point; provided that at the beginning of the session there is an express petition from the party representative and/or coalition that presented the second of the candidates reported.
The total counting of the ballot can also be achieved if, at the end of the joint counting, the difference between the successful candidate and the second-place candidate is equal to or less than a percentage point, provided that there is an express petition from the representative of the political party whose candidate was second, in which case the electoral packages that were the subject of the partial counting will be excluded.
It should be noted that this is the situation of the election of Morelia, where according to the PREP, the difference between the first and second place is only 0.16 percent, even without counting the votes of 129 of the 923 total minutes.
